        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/30135",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jpieper",
                        "name": "jpieper",
                        "displayName": "Jan Pieper",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Zend_Translate is only a \"factory\" like class to instantiate translate adapters. Why aren't you instantiating your class directly?\n\n{code}$translate = new My_Translate_Adapter_Foo($data, $locale, $options);{code}\n\nIt isn't the finest way but it should help.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jpieper",
                        "name": "jpieper",
                        "displayName": "Jan Pieper",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-04-15T04:33:27.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-04-15T04:33:27.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/30136",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=radhad",
                        "name": "radhad",
                        "displayName": "Dennis Becker",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This is a possible way, I haven't checked this solution and I just thought about a more flexible factory pattern implementation, maybe similar to the new Zend_Application component where you can add more plugin paths.\n\nThis is just a small idea from my side :)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=radhad",
                        "name": "radhad",
                        "displayName": "Dennis Becker",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-04-15T04:54:03.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-04-15T04:54:03.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/30137",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Sorry, but I don't see a problem with this code...\nYou can use ANY properitary adapter by simply giving it:\n\n{code}\n$translate = new Zend_Translate('My_Own_Properitary_Translation_Adapter', $file, $locale, $options);\n{code}\n\nIt is even written within the manual within a own chapter how to do this:\nhttp:\/\/framework.zend.com\/manual\/en\/zend.translate.adapter.html#zend.translate.adapter.selfwritten",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-04-15T05:04:15.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-04-15T05:04:15.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/30138",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=radhad",
                        "name": "radhad",
                        "displayName": "Dennis Becker",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Sorry, seems to be my fault. When I did the tests, I had not seen this chapter in the manual!\n\nI will try this and will report, if it worked for me or not. Thanks for the hint to the manual, it seems I'll have to re-read some hcapters ;)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
